subsection.def:
Board
                    (管理局) means the registration board
                established under section 4;

Chairman
                    (主席) means the Chairman of the Board elected
                under section 6;

Council
                    (理事會) means the Council of the
                Institute;

register
                    (註冊紀錄冊) means the register established under
                    section 8;

Registrar
                    (註冊主任) means the Registrar appointed under
                    section 11;

paragraph.content:
having been summoned by an inquiry committee to attend as a witness or to
                    produce a document or other thing under section 25 without reasonable
                    excuse refuses or fails to do so;

attends as a witness before an inquiry committee and, without lawful
                    excuse, refuses or fails to answer any question put to him by the inquiry
                    committee;

obtains registration as a registered architect for himself or any other
                    person by means of any misleading, false or fraudulent representation or,
                    statement, either oral or in writing;

impersonates or falsely represents himself as being the person referred to
                    in any certificate or document presented to the Board or an inquiry committee in
                    connection with its functions under this Ordinance;

subparagraph.content:
any initials or abbreviations of words intended to cause, or which may
                        reasonably cause, any person to believe that the person using the initials
                        or abbreviations is on the register;
